(NFA To DFA Visual Simulator - Step By Step Code Explanation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. PROJECT GOAL) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This project is a separate NFA to DFA visual simulator. The user manually enters an NFA,) Tj
T*
(then the program converts it into a DFA and prints clean transition tables.) Tj
T*
(The full path is: manual NFA input -> transition storage -> subset construction -> DFA) Tj
T*
(table -> string testing.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. MAIN.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Main.java contains the main method. It creates the UI object and starts the menu. The) Tj
T*
(entry point stays very small so the rest of the logic is in focused classes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. UI.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(UI.java controls the console experience. Option 1 lets the user enter a custom NFA.) Tj
T*
(Option 2 displays the NFA table. Option 3 converts the NFA to a DFA. Option 4 displays) Tj
T*
(the DFA table. Option 5 tests strings. Option 6 loads the professor demo NFA.) Tj
T*
(For custom NFA input, the user enters states, alphabet, start state, final states, and) Tj
T*
(transitions. Epsilon transitions can be written as eps, epsilon, or #.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. STATE.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(State.java represents one NFA state using a name such as q0. It stores transitions in a) Tj
T*
(map from symbol to a set of states. A set is used because an NFA may move to multiple) Tj
T*
(states on the same symbol.) Tj
T*
(The class also defines a special internal epsilon symbol. When printed, that symbol) Tj
T*
(appears as eps.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. NFA.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(NFA.java stores all manually entered NFA data: states, alphabet, start state, final) Tj
T*
(states, and transitions.) Tj
T*
(It validates important input rules, such as unknown states and symbols not found in the) Tj
T*
(alphabet. It also has describe\(\), which prints the NFA table for presentation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6. SUBSETCONSTRUCTION.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(SubsetConstruction performs the standard NFA to DFA conversion. A DFA state is) Tj
T*
(represented as a set of NFA states.) Tj
T*
(The first DFA state is epsilon-closure of the NFA start state. For each DFA state and) Tj
T*
(symbol, the program computes move\(\) and then epsilonClosure\(\). If the result is new, it) Tj
T*
(becomes a new DFA state.) Tj
T*
(The empty set can become a DFA dead state when no NFA transition exists for a symbol.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(7. DFASTATE.JAVA AND DFA.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
