(DFAState.java stores the set of NFA states represented by one DFA state. It also records) Tj
T*
(whether that DFA state is final. A DFA state is final if its NFA set contains at least) Tj
T*
(one NFA final state.) Tj
T*
(DFA.java stores the DFA start state, final states, alphabet, and all transitions. Its) Tj
T*
(describe\(\) method prints the DFA state meanings and transition table.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(8. TRANSITIONTABLEPRINTER.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(TransitionTablePrinter is only responsible for display. It prints NFA and DFA transition) Tj
T*
(tables in aligned columns. Start states are marked with -> and final states are marked) Tj
T*
(with *.) Tj
T*
(Keeping this code separate makes the automata classes easier to understand, because) Tj
T*
(display formatting is not mixed with conversion logic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(9. STRINGTESTER.JAVA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(StringTester tests a string by starting from the DFA start state and following one) Tj
T*
(transition per character.) Tj
T*
(If a character is not in the alphabet, the string is rejected. If the final reached) Tj
T*
(state is final, the string is accepted. The class also prints the trace of states) Tj
T*
(visited.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(10. PROFESSOR DEMO) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Menu option 6 loads a ready-made NFA. The language is all strings over {a,b} that end) Tj
T*
(with ab.) Tj
T*
(Demo NFA states: q0, q1, q2. Alphabet: a, b. Start: q0. Final: q2. Transitions: q0 on a) Tj
T*
(to q0 and q1; q0 on b to q0; q1 on b to q2.) Tj
T*
(Expected accepted strings: ab, aab, babab. Expected rejected strings: a, aba, bbb.) Tj
T*
(After the demo runs, the DFA remains loaded, so the user can choose option 5 and enter) Tj
T*
(any custom test string.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(11. HOW TO RUN) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Command line: cd NFAToDFAVisualSimulator, then javac -d out src\\*.java, then java -cp) Tj
T*
(out Main.) Tj
T*
(In IntelliJ: open the NFAToDFAVisualSimulator folder, mark src as Sources Root if) Tj
T*
(needed, open Main.java, and click Run.) Tj
T*
(In NetBeans: create a Java project, copy the src files into its src folder, set Main as) Tj
T*
(the main class, and run.) Tj
T*
() Tj
